title: Change CODEOWNERS for docs to be approved by any cserv or ceng member
body:
# Pull Request Documentation

**PLEASE READ** - Fill in this section to generate evidence as may be required in an audit.
- See https://github.com/sky-uk/gtvd-azman2-aws/tree/main/docs for documentation

## Type of change requested

Resident changes
- [ ] Change membership of a team
- [ ] Team membership review / setting last approved date
- [ ] Manage access to a new IAM role
- [ ] User Access Review (UAR)

Admin changes
- [x] Change a CODEOWNER
- [ ] Documentation change
- [ ] Manage a new AWS account
- [ ] Code change

## Description of change

Update CODEOWNERS file to add `/docs` to be reviewed by any member of the central services and cloud engineering teams.

## Reason for change

Currently, when we update any files under `/docs`, the @sky-uk/azman-cloud-engineering-owners are the only CODEOWNERS. Since there are only 3 members, If they are busy/absent, we will be unable to merge our documentation to the main branch. 

We propose to add the central services and cloud engineering team members to be the codeowners of anything under `/docs`.
